== Overview == The group includes 13 {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofuns|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}} and 3 {{ill|rectangular mounds|ja|前方後方墳|1=zenpō-kōhō-fun|12=draft|12=draft}}, making it one of the most significant large-scale kofun groups in Japan. Most of the primary mounds in this group are considered early-period kofun. Throughout the early {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, very few regions aside from the central areas such as {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|12=draft|12=draft}} (modern-day {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}}) experienced sustained kofun construction.
