{{One source|date=2013rd year 10月21日 (月) 08:09 (UTC)}} '''Unai Aotsu Kofun Group''' ({{ill|Unai Aotsu Kofun Group|ja|宇内青津古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) is a {{ill|kofun group|ja|古墳群|1=Kofun cluster|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Aizubange|ja|会津坂下町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It consists of 16 Kofuns.
== Overview == The group includes 13 {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofuns|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and 3 {{ill|rectangular mounds|ja|前方後方墳|1=zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, making it one of the most significant large-scale kofun groups in Japan. Most of the primary mounds in this group are considered early-period kofun. Throughout the early {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, very few regions aside from the central areas such as {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (modern-day {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) experienced sustained kofun construction.
== Notable Kofun == * {{ill|Kamegamori-Chinjumori Kofun|ja|亀ヶ森・鎮守森古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - A National Historic Site. Kamegamori Kofun, at 127 meters in length, is the largest in the prefecture. * {{ill|Kinegamori Kofun|ja|杵ガ森古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Among the oldest kofun in the Tohoku region, constructed in the early 4th century. * Usagamori Kofun * Nagaimae no Yama Kofun - Features a gabled ceiling stone coffin, constructed in the early 5th century. * Kokuzomori Kofun * Tenjinmen Kofun * {{ill|Haizukayama Kofun|ja|灰塚山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * Miyahigashi No. 1 Kofun * Raijinzan No. 1 Kofun * Morikita No. 1 Kofun * Kajiyama No. 4 Kofun * Dezakiyama No. 1 Kofun * Dezakiyama No. 2 Kofun * Dezakiyama No. 3 Kofun * Dezakiyama No. 4 Kofun
Additionally, it is said that a kofun called Maigamori Kofun existed between Kinegamori and Usagamori Kofun.
== References == * Hidehito Tsuji, *The Foundation of Tohoku Kofun Research: Aizu Otsukayama Kofun*, "Learning from Historical Sites" Series 029, Shinseisha, 2006. == See Also == * {{ill|List of Kofun in Japan|ja|日本の古墳一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
