== Overview == The group includes 13 {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofuns|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keyhole-shaped Kofuns|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenpokoenfun|qq=}} and 3 {{ill|rectangular mounds|ja|前方後方墳|1=zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/rectangular mounds|13=User:Immanuelle/zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=}}, making it one of the most significant large-scale kofun groups in Japan. Most of the primary mounds in this group are considered early-period kofun. Throughout the early {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun period|qq=}}, very few regions aside from the central areas such as {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Province|qq=}} (modern-day {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara Prefecture|qq=}}) experienced sustained kofun construction.
